01:07.302 --> 01:10.304
It tastes better
because it's more expensive.

01:10.339 --> 01:12.539
It's the premium brand
and it's priced accordingly.

01:12.574 --> 01:14.441
Price is irrelevant
because the question is

01:14.476 --> 01:16.510
does it taste
better than butter?

01:16.544 --> 01:19.847
Butter is actually fresh.
Margarine is indestructible.

01:19.881 --> 01:22.750
He's right because he's only
comparing different margarines

01:22.784 --> 01:25.719
and margarine has a 70%
market share over butter.

01:25.754 --> 01:28.821
But it's hard to say
any brand is luxury

01:28.856 --> 01:30.823
<i>when although Fleischmann's</i>
<i>is the most expensive</i>

01:30.858 --> 01:32.592
and Blue Bonnet,
owned by the same company,

01:32.626 --> 01:35.160
is the least expensive,
the difference is only pennies.

01:35.195 --> 01:37.397
45 cents a pound
is the highest.

01:37.431 --> 01:40.533
29 is the lowest.
That's 50% more expensive.

01:40.567 --> 01:42.134
Fleischmann's is Chivas Regal.

01:42.168 --> 01:44.035
Still half the price of butter.

01:44.069 --> 01:46.371
- It's Budweiser.
- But what's the market share?

01:46.406 --> 01:48.072
I just said it's much
higher than butter.

01:48.107 --> 01:50.041
Seeing as I have
the ear of the client,

01:50.075 --> 01:54.012
it's my recommendation
we go on taste alone.

01:54.046 --> 01:55.313
Peggy!

01:57.383 --> 01:59.517
Don, I agree with you.

02:03.822 --> 02:05.523
You're in the market
buying margarine.

02:05.557 --> 02:07.525
Okay.

02:07.559 --> 02:10.160
What goes through your mind?

02:10.193 --> 02:13.263
Mouthwatering, savory,
delicious taste?

02:13.298 --> 02:17.400
Or mouthwatering, savory,
delicious taste and price?

02:17.435 --> 02:19.969
I'd buy the cheaper one.

02:20.003 --> 02:22.906
There's one for 45 cents
a pound and one for 29.

02:22.940 --> 02:25.341
Which one do you think
is gonna taste better?

02:25.375 --> 02:28.445
It's a terrible gamble to tell a client
that their product is expensive.

02:28.479 --> 02:31.880
Shh.
Let her answer.

02:34.016 --> 02:35.984
I don't know.

02:36.018 --> 02:37.486
They both sound good.

02:37.520 --> 02:38.821
Really?

02:38.855 --> 02:40.522
Does everyone agree with yours?

02:40.557 --> 02:42.424
It's not his and mine.
Everyone has an opinion.

02:42.459 --> 02:43.892
We haven't heard it,
but I'm sure they do.

02:43.927 --> 02:45.293
I like Don's.

02:45.328 --> 02:47.095
What did Harry say?

02:48.296 --> 02:50.264
I feel strongly both ways.

02:52.067 --> 02:53.668
They're both so good.

02:53.702 --> 02:56.637
I'd probably ask someone to run
them by the client on the sly.

02:56.672 --> 02:58.272
The meeting's tomorrow.

03:02.644 --> 03:04.511
You know what, Don?
Let's go with yours.

03:05.713 --> 03:07.981
Nah, I'm not even
gonna be there.

03:09.617 --> 03:12.151
You should go with whatever
you're most comfortable with.

03:22.496 --> 03:24.096
Could you get me another
copy of that research?

03:24.130 --> 03:25.965
I want to make it big
on a board.

03:28.702 --> 03:31.704
Did you see that?
He didn't even turn around.

03:31.738 --> 03:33.939
- Yep.
- Oh, it speaks.

03:33.974 --> 03:35.840
Come on, I wasn't gonna
get in the middle of that.

03:35.875 --> 03:37.174
You suddenly dumber than Peggy?

03:37.209 --> 03:39.243
So you're content in silence?

03:39.277 --> 03:41.112
I'm content with reality.

03:41.146 --> 03:43.014
You know what this place looks
like to the outside world?

03:43.048 --> 03:45.082
A mess. We don't
even have a name.

03:45.117 --> 03:47.685
- We're the '27 Yankees.
- Says who?

03:47.720 --> 03:50.655
Pete, you want to get
your balls tickled?

03:50.689 --> 03:52.155
Go see a headhunter.

03:52.189 --> 03:53.891
Are you leaving?

03:53.925 --> 03:56.259
Look, when things settle down,
I'm gonna be a partner.

03:56.293 --> 03:59.262
For the time being, it's nice to know
that the water's warm out there.

04:08.238 --> 04:10.540
Did you lose something?

04:10.574 --> 04:12.708
Yes.

04:12.743 --> 04:14.977
I was looking for...

04:15.012 --> 04:18.014
how do you say, a pen
to write something down.

04:18.048 --> 04:21.951
Oh, well, the desk
is littered with them.

04:25.154 --> 04:27.022
Would you like a drink?

04:27.056 --> 04:28.857
Certainly, Colette.

04:28.891 --> 04:30.792
Although this is
my husband's office.

04:30.826 --> 04:32.126
I should be offering you one.

04:32.161 --> 04:33.862
It is no trouble at all.

04:33.896 --> 04:35.764
We're a lot alike.

04:35.798 --> 04:38.967
We're both interested
in things that belong to me.

04:42.871 --> 04:45.773
I don't know what
you're talking about.

04:45.807 --> 04:47.741
I don't know what
your relationship is

04:47.776 --> 04:50.010
with my husband, but it's over.

04:50.045 --> 04:52.613
<i>Cut. Let's clean
up in there and back up.</i>

04:55.816 --> 04:57.850
<i>Megan, sweetheart, what are
you doing on the floor?</i>

04:57.885 --> 04:59.852
The script said
to spill the drink.

04:59.887 --> 05:01.654
<i>It doesn't say to clean it up.</i>

05:01.689 --> 05:03.355
I just thought...

05:03.390 --> 05:05.224
<i>Your sister Corinne</i>
<i>is the maid.</i>

05:05.258 --> 05:08.527
<i>You're Colette right now.</i>
<i>She's blonde, classy.</i>

05:08.562 --> 05:11.597
<i>We need you to make</i>
<i>these women different, honey.</i>

05:11.631 --> 05:14.066
<i>Let's take it</i>
<i>from the top, ladies.</i>

05:14.100 --> 05:15.901
Don't worry about it.

05:21.641 --> 05:24.610
I think Phyllis left for the day, but
I never saw the boards for tomorrow.

05:24.644 --> 05:27.345
- Stan has them.
- Ah.

05:27.379 --> 05:29.981
- What are you working on?
- Royal Hawaiian.

05:30.015 --> 05:32.850
- How's that going?
- I'm sure you will tell me.

05:32.884 --> 05:34.819
I will.

05:34.853 --> 05:36.487
I'll look at it very carefully

05:36.521 --> 05:39.456
and then I'll formulate
an educated opinion.

05:39.491 --> 05:41.792
You should try it sometime.
It's what professionals do.

05:41.827 --> 05:43.760
Don.

05:44.962 --> 05:46.863
You've been debating
that for weeks.

05:46.897 --> 05:49.565
- You both have a point.
- I'm not paying you to be a diplomat.

05:49.600 --> 05:51.467
Well, you're both
more experienced than me.

05:51.502 --> 05:53.236
I don't know
that my opinion matters.

05:53.270 --> 05:54.704
Your opinion matters.

05:54.739 --> 05:56.806
Now what do you think
is the best way to go?

05:56.841 --> 05:58.708
- It's somewhere in the middle.
- No, Peggy.

05:58.743 --> 06:00.809
There's a right
and there's a wrong.

06:00.844 --> 06:02.544
How could that be?

06:02.578 --> 06:05.347
What you're really saying is
there's you and there's him.

06:05.381 --> 06:08.350
And I don't know how I became in charge
of turning this into a collaboration.

06:08.384 --> 06:10.552
Isn't that your job?

06:10.586 --> 06:12.521
You're both demanding
and you're both pigheaded.

06:12.555 --> 06:14.589
You're the same person
sometimes.

06:14.624 --> 06:16.758
The difference is that
he's interested in the idea

06:16.792 --> 06:18.592
and you're interested
in your idea.

06:20.763 --> 06:23.430
He's interested in his idea.
Don't let him fool you.

06:23.465 --> 06:25.900
Well, he never makes me
feel this way.

06:25.934 --> 06:27.969
He doesn't know you.

06:42.917 --> 06:45.652
Henry said you were leaving.

06:45.687 --> 06:47.353
He just had to make
one phone call,

06:47.388 --> 06:48.954
which turned out to be two.

06:48.989 --> 06:50.322
Full house, I see.

06:50.356 --> 06:52.591
He should be off in a minute.

06:52.625 --> 06:54.426
Well, he's a lucky man.
But not as lucky as me,

06:54.460 --> 06:56.162
because I wanted to be
alone with you all night.

06:56.196 --> 06:58.330
He'll be out in a minute.

06:58.364 --> 07:01.633
I don't think you heard.

07:01.668 --> 07:05.937
I want to be alone
with <i>you</i> all night.

07:05.971 --> 07:08.606
Mr. Dell, I have
three children.

07:08.640 --> 07:10.141
I don't care.

07:11.410 --> 07:13.678
No, look at me.

07:13.713 --> 07:15.680
Can you believe
I've had three children?

07:25.223 --> 07:27.457
How was your evening, Stew?

07:27.491 --> 07:29.093
Raised a lot of money.

07:29.127 --> 07:31.695
Darling, shall we?

07:38.836 --> 07:42.171
- What's going on?
- There was an incident.

07:42.206 --> 07:44.006
Oh, my God!

07:44.041 --> 07:46.542
- They hurt you.
- I'm fine, honey.

07:46.576 --> 07:49.678
He was getting off the subway
and two guys stabbed him.

07:49.713 --> 07:52.114
- What?
- Hey, I don't want to worry her, man.

07:52.148 --> 07:54.249
I'm sorry, but I'm trying
to get it straight.

07:54.283 --> 07:57.485
And, frankly, she should know
so she can keep up her defense.

07:57.519 --> 07:59.621
- Jesus, what happened?
- Are we done here?

07:59.655 --> 08:03.358
For a reporter,
this is missing detail.

08:03.392 --> 08:05.460
And if you'd waited
at the hospital,

08:05.494 --> 08:07.662
as you were instructed,
we'd be done.

08:07.696 --> 08:10.297
But for some reason you didn't.

08:10.331 --> 08:12.032
I filled out the form.

08:12.067 --> 08:14.701
Come on, were they colored
or Puerto Rican?

08:14.736 --> 08:16.336
Or white?

08:16.371 --> 08:18.773
I'm from Brooklyn and I
always keep my eyes down.

08:18.807 --> 08:21.242
Could you describe the shoes?

08:21.276 --> 08:24.077
Look, both of us have done
our civic duty.

08:24.111 --> 08:26.545
So, respectfully,
I think you should go.

08:32.253 --> 08:34.486
I'd get one of these.

08:36.456 --> 08:38.424
Good evening, ma'am.

08:40.193 --> 08:42.160
Can you believe
those questions?

08:42.195 --> 08:45.164
- Fascist pig!
- Shut up, Abe!

08:45.198 --> 08:46.631
You don't know
what they look like?

08:46.666 --> 08:48.100
You have a photographic memory.

08:48.134 --> 08:49.734
Peg, I'm not gonna
give him an excuse

08:49.769 --> 08:51.503
to shake down every kid that
walks through this neighborhood.

08:51.537 --> 08:53.238
What about the one
that stabbed you?

08:53.273 --> 08:55.007
This is a fucking police state

08:55.041 --> 08:56.707
and we're gonna
have to fight, okay?

08:56.741 --> 08:58.375
They did it in Prague.
They did it in Paris.

08:58.410 --> 09:00.044
And, believe it or not, we're
gonna have to do it here, too.

09:00.078 --> 09:02.180
That doesn't mean
protecting criminals.

09:02.214 --> 09:05.850
Listen, baby, it's my right to
tell whomever whatever I want.

09:05.884 --> 09:09.086
But you can keep talking because
everything you say is going in my story.

09:09.121 --> 09:10.654
What are you talking about?

09:10.689 --> 09:13.756
It's just fascinating,
the attitudes I'm encountering.

09:13.791 --> 09:16.092
But why would you side
with the cops?

09:16.127 --> 09:18.094
I don't know.

09:22.666 --> 09:24.968
I read about this.

09:27.271 --> 09:31.040
You obviously had
a traumatic experience

09:31.074 --> 09:32.842
not unlike combat.

09:32.876 --> 09:37.213
So I'm going to let you do
whatever you're doing.

09:37.247 --> 09:39.448
Don't patronize me.

09:39.482 --> 09:42.284
Those kids have no other
recourse in this system.

09:42.319 --> 09:44.585
- They're animals.
- They were brought here by slave ships.

09:44.619 --> 09:46.254
Well, I was
brought here by you.

09:46.288 --> 09:48.723
I don't care if I take a loss,
I'm gonna sell this shithole.

09:48.757 --> 09:52.327
You're worried about me
and I love you for it.

09:54.863 --> 09:56.830
Now, I don't think
I can type with this thing.

09:56.865 --> 09:58.732
Get my Olympia. Help me
get some of this down.

09:59.800 --> 10:01.701
I'm going to bed.

10:10.577 --> 10:12.211
This is nice.

10:12.246 --> 10:15.414
It's Thursday.
Told you I was making dinner.

10:18.618 --> 10:20.586
Sit down.

10:24.358 --> 10:26.457
How was your day?

10:26.492 --> 10:28.226
How was yours?

10:28.261 --> 10:29.961
Hmm.

10:29.996 --> 10:31.296
It was...

10:31.330 --> 10:33.365
Ugh, it was terrible.

10:33.399 --> 10:35.566
I don't even know
if I want to talk about it.

10:37.169 --> 10:39.237
What's for dinner?

10:39.272 --> 10:40.872
I think they hate me.

10:40.907 --> 10:42.740
They just gave you
a second part.

10:43.876 --> 10:45.443
I feel like an idiot
because they keep telling me

10:45.477 --> 10:47.278
they can't tell
the twins apart.

10:47.312 --> 10:49.980
I think I'm playing them
very differently.

10:50.015 --> 10:51.883
It's not like
it's never been done before.

10:51.917 --> 10:53.584
Exactly.

10:53.619 --> 10:56.854
I told Mel I didn't want
to be a cliché.

10:56.889 --> 11:01.124
Then he starts rapping about how
they're two halves of the same person

11:01.158 --> 11:04.761
and they want the same thing, but they're
trying to get it in different ways.

11:16.005 --> 11:19.241
Listen, would you mind if we
just go in and turn on the set?

11:19.275 --> 11:20.776
I'm really not hungry.

11:20.811 --> 11:22.678
Did you have a bad day?

11:24.714 --> 11:26.148
I'm just tired.

11:27.818 --> 11:30.852
Go lay down.
I'll clean up.

11:32.287 --> 11:35.557
I already packed your bag
for Bobby's camp.

11:37.460 --> 11:39.561
Tomorrow's another day.

11:47.268 --> 11:49.903
John, could you give us
some privacy?

11:55.076 --> 11:56.810
Was the evening a success?

11:56.845 --> 11:58.445
You tell me.

12:00.982 --> 12:03.549
Well, I--

12:03.584 --> 12:06.185
I found it fascinating as usual

12:06.219 --> 12:08.821
watching you work your magic.

12:08.856 --> 12:11.056
And while you were watching me,

12:11.091 --> 12:14.259
everyone was watching you,
weren't they?

12:21.233 --> 12:23.802
Stewart did everything
but grab your ass.

12:26.839 --> 12:28.540
I didn't notice.

12:28.574 --> 12:30.542
What did he say to you?

12:33.646 --> 12:35.946
I don't want to get
anyone in trouble.

12:35.981 --> 12:37.948
Word for word.

12:41.953 --> 12:44.488
He said he wanted
to be alone with me.

12:47.592 --> 12:50.293
What else?

12:50.328 --> 12:52.294
All night.

13:02.873 --> 13:05.107
Daddy, I don't want him
running on the steps.

13:05.142 --> 13:07.108
Why not?
Kids are supposed to run.

13:07.143 --> 13:09.711
Ellery, come down.

13:09.746 --> 13:11.479
We don't have any steps
in the apartment.

13:11.514 --> 13:12.848
He's not good at them.

13:15.317 --> 13:17.886
So what do you think, girls?

13:17.921 --> 13:19.621
See any resemblance?

13:19.656 --> 13:21.657
He's very handsome.

13:21.691 --> 13:23.658
So, Ellery, take a good look.

13:23.692 --> 13:26.627
Who's your type?

13:26.662 --> 13:28.462
Hello, Margaret.

13:28.496 --> 13:30.130
I'll tell you mine later.

13:30.165 --> 13:32.066
It's nice to see you.

13:32.100 --> 13:34.902
Oh, he's precious.
How old is he?

13:34.937 --> 13:38.305
He's four. He's having a
special day with Pop-pop.

13:38.339 --> 13:40.406
We're going to the zoo
and maybe the movies.

13:40.441 --> 13:41.975
So it's just a regular workday.

13:43.644 --> 13:45.511
Don't fill him full of junk.

13:45.546 --> 13:47.547
Can't promise that.

13:49.684 --> 13:51.417
Wave good-bye, swabby.

13:51.452 --> 13:52.752
We're shoving off.

13:56.355 --> 13:58.190
How many times
have you met with Harry?

13:58.224 --> 14:00.726
Too many. Don't waste
my time like Crane.

14:00.760 --> 14:02.962
I'm a headhunter,
not a fan club.

14:02.996 --> 14:05.664
Fine, let's talk about me.

14:05.699 --> 14:07.733
Let's talk about Burt Peterson.

14:07.767 --> 14:09.902
I got him a vice
presidency at McCann.

14:09.936 --> 14:11.903
If he keeps his head down,
he's set for life.

14:11.937 --> 14:16.373
But the merger was fresh.
I don't know your situation.

14:16.408 --> 14:18.009
You weren't very straight
on the phone.

14:18.043 --> 14:19.644
You think they're gonna
cut you loose?

14:19.678 --> 14:22.513
How come you didn't
get yourself a job?

14:23.849 --> 14:25.917
That's a Yankee wrinkle.

14:25.951 --> 14:28.752
- You interested in my business?
- No.

14:28.786 --> 14:32.789
Well, if we sat down
a couple of months ago,

14:32.824 --> 14:34.758
this would have been
a different conversation.

14:34.792 --> 14:36.627
Nothing's changed.
I'll show you my Rolodex.

14:36.661 --> 14:39.896
It's not that. It's your lack of a
role in the management structure.

14:39.931 --> 14:43.065
Sterling Cooper Draper Pryce
Cutler Gleason and Chaough?

14:43.100 --> 14:44.500
Who the hell's in charge?

14:44.534 --> 14:46.535
Two of those men
are as dead as doornails.

14:46.569 --> 14:48.938
There's still a lot of chiefs
and only a couple of Indians.

14:48.972 --> 14:50.973
And a lot of questions.

14:51.008 --> 14:52.808
What the hell
happened with Vicks?

14:54.778 --> 14:56.712
So...

14:56.747 --> 14:58.447
paint me a new portrait.

14:58.481 --> 15:00.882
I'm glad you said that.

15:00.916 --> 15:03.284
How about seeing things
from the client side?

15:03.318 --> 15:06.187
There's a head of marketing job in
Wichita that you'd be perfect for.

15:06.221 --> 15:07.756
Anything back here on Earth?

15:07.790 --> 15:09.791
You know,

15:09.825 --> 15:11.259
I've always liked you,
Campbell,

15:11.293 --> 15:13.028
so forgive me for saying this,

15:13.062 --> 15:15.329
but if you do a little better,
I can do a lot better.

15:15.364 --> 15:17.632
I don't know
what else I can do.

15:20.269 --> 15:22.603
I've been you

15:22.638 --> 15:24.104
and I went on interviews

15:24.139 --> 15:27.441
and I realized I was filling
the room with desperation.

15:28.943 --> 15:31.344
Five cents worth
of free advice.

15:31.379 --> 15:33.313
You've got to spend
less time in this place

15:33.347 --> 15:34.648
and more at home.

15:34.682 --> 15:37.050
This is a reluctant necessity.

15:37.084 --> 15:38.552
My mother's run amok.

15:39.787 --> 15:42.622
Pete, one day
I looked in the mirror

15:42.657 --> 15:45.325
and I realized I had regrets
because I didn't understand

15:45.359 --> 15:47.060
the wellspring
of my confidence.

15:47.094 --> 15:48.260
Gin?

15:48.295 --> 15:50.128
My family.

15:50.163 --> 15:53.065
My family is a constant
distraction.

15:54.234 --> 15:55.734
You better manage that

15:55.768 --> 15:57.570
or you're not gonna
manage anything.

16:07.012 --> 16:08.680
Hey, buddy.

16:19.757 --> 16:21.458
Can you help me?

16:21.492 --> 16:23.860
I'm occupied
at the moment, sir.

16:36.506 --> 16:37.806
Hello there.

16:39.243 --> 16:42.378
Oh.
Are you lost, too?

16:42.412 --> 16:44.547
Not yet.

16:44.581 --> 16:46.782
I'm trying to get some gas.

16:46.816 --> 16:48.851
Lady asked for directions.

16:48.885 --> 16:50.653
Fill 'er up with regular.

16:53.289 --> 16:54.756
Where's Henry?

16:54.790 --> 16:57.259
He's coming tomorrow.

16:57.293 --> 16:59.394
I'm surprised you
were able to get away.

16:59.428 --> 17:02.764
Where are you staying?

17:02.798 --> 17:04.665
Somewhere over here.

17:08.770 --> 17:11.305
Just go down here. Stay
on here a mile and a half

17:11.339 --> 17:13.473
till you get to the big mill.
Make a left.

17:13.508 --> 17:15.608
Go back through town
till the railroad tracks.

17:15.644 --> 17:17.144
Hang a right over the bridge

17:17.178 --> 17:19.212
and then you come
to the little mill.

17:19.247 --> 17:21.181
Do any of the roads have names?

17:21.214 --> 17:23.583
Follow me.

17:30.432 --> 17:31.733
Fleischmann's just called.

17:31.767 --> 17:34.268
See? You were worried
for nothing.

17:34.302 --> 17:37.304
Well, they just requested some more
recent figures on market share.

17:37.339 --> 17:38.840
I'll handle it.

17:38.874 --> 17:40.541
Peggy, may I speak with you?
Go ahead.

17:45.947 --> 17:47.380
What the hell were you
doing back there?

17:47.414 --> 17:49.215
You didn't want me to talk.

17:49.250 --> 17:52.019
I didn't talk. That was the plan.
Did you want me to talk?

17:52.053 --> 17:54.587
- No, you touched my hand.
- What?

17:54.622 --> 17:56.422
When you handed me the board.

17:56.457 --> 17:57.990
What?
No, I didn't.

17:58.025 --> 18:01.160
Yes, you did. And you can't
do that in a presentation.

18:01.194 --> 18:03.796
I doubt anyone saw that because
I didn't even know I did it.

18:03.830 --> 18:06.832
It jarred me. And when I finally
caught up, then you smiled.

18:06.867 --> 18:09.201
You can't smile
at me like that.

18:09.235 --> 18:10.569
I never should have kissed you.

18:16.375 --> 18:19.944
I assumed we were
forgetting about that.

18:22.314 --> 18:23.915
I forgot it.

18:23.949 --> 18:26.651
Well, I haven't.

18:28.353 --> 18:30.320
Oh.

18:32.157 --> 18:34.491
What an old tune.

18:34.525 --> 18:37.661
The boss in love
with his protégé.

18:37.696 --> 18:40.597
Is this all me?
Because that'll help.

18:41.632 --> 18:43.466
I think about it.

18:45.635 --> 18:48.104
Well, we can't. I have
someone, you have someone.

18:48.138 --> 18:51.407
And believe me, I've considered
it a lot further than that.

18:51.441 --> 18:54.643
I didn't know
you felt this way.

18:58.949 --> 19:01.416
I don't want to,
that's the point.

19:01.450 --> 19:03.885
Now I realize I never
should have brought it up.

19:05.722 --> 19:07.889
Do you want me
to work someplace else?

19:07.924 --> 19:09.557
No.

19:09.592 --> 19:10.926
Of course not.

19:22.104 --> 19:24.304
Come on, you have to do it.

19:26.474 --> 19:28.075
And the left.

19:28.110 --> 19:32.213
♪ Father Abraham had
seven sons, seven sons ♪

19:32.247 --> 19:35.481
♪ And seven sons
had Father Abraham. ♪

19:35.515 --> 19:37.550
Daddy, you came!

19:39.586 --> 19:41.054
You didn't tell him I was here?

19:41.088 --> 19:43.422
I wanted it to be a surprise.

19:43.457 --> 19:45.158
You catch any fish?

19:45.192 --> 19:48.161
Damn it, I made you a wallet,
but it's back in my cabin.

19:48.195 --> 19:49.461
Bobby, language.

19:49.495 --> 19:51.463
We'll get it later.

19:54.901 --> 19:57.469
Mommy said we can have
anything we want.

19:57.503 --> 19:59.872
Hi!

19:59.906 --> 20:01.573
This is my mom and dad.

20:03.376 --> 20:05.643
That's Bobby Two.
He's shy.

20:05.677 --> 20:08.146
Are you Bobby or Bobby One?

20:08.180 --> 20:09.613
I'm Bobby Five.

20:09.648 --> 20:11.849
It's sad. There's no
Bobby One anymore.

20:11.884 --> 20:13.617
Because of Bobby Kennedy?

20:13.652 --> 20:15.586
No, he went home.

20:15.620 --> 20:18.189
Do you want me to get the
waitress so you can get a drink?

20:19.724 --> 20:22.058
- Is that possible?
- No.

20:22.093 --> 20:25.061
Mommy's having a chef salad
and I'm having a cheeseburger.

20:25.096 --> 20:26.863
What do you want
so I can order?

20:26.898 --> 20:29.132
What's good here?

20:29.167 --> 20:31.334
I'm afraid nothing.

20:31.368 --> 20:33.569
Daddy, I want
to teach you this song.

20:33.604 --> 20:35.272
Just do what I do.

20:35.306 --> 20:39.541
