20:43.113 --> 20:45.281
♪ And they never
laughed, ha ha ♪

20:45.315 --> 20:47.216
♪ And they never cried,
boo-hoo ♪

20:47.250 --> 20:49.919
♪ All they did
was go like this ♪

20:49.953 --> 20:51.553
♪ With the right ♪

20:51.587 --> 20:55.723
♪ Father Abraham had
seven sons, seven sons ♪

20:55.757 --> 20:59.093
♪ Seven sons
had Father Abraham ♪

20:59.128 --> 21:01.129
♪ And they never
laughed, ha ha ♪

21:01.163 --> 21:02.964
♪ And they never cried,
boo-hoo ♪

21:02.998 --> 21:06.467
♪ All they did was go like this,
with the right... ♪

21:06.501 --> 21:08.836
Can I walk you out?

21:10.004 --> 21:12.105
Certainly, if you
don't mind waiting.

21:16.010 --> 21:18.011
I need your advice.

21:18.046 --> 21:20.580
And, well,
it's of a personal nature

21:20.614 --> 21:22.850
and thus above Clara's
security clearance.

21:22.884 --> 21:24.751
How can I help you?

21:26.519 --> 21:29.255
Do you feel my attention
to business has been dilute?

21:38.365 --> 21:40.499
How personal
is this conversation?

21:42.001 --> 21:45.170
I'm being pulled
in a million directions.

21:45.204 --> 21:48.306
My wife, my child, my mother.

21:48.341 --> 21:50.175
I can't solve
those problems, Pete.

21:50.209 --> 21:51.943
I have those problems.

21:51.978 --> 21:53.711
I live with my mother.

21:53.746 --> 21:56.081
Has your mother exhausted
every nursing agency?

21:56.115 --> 21:58.249
No, but she's exhausted me.

21:58.283 --> 22:00.817
Well...

22:00.852 --> 22:03.153
the options are
my home and a home,

22:03.188 --> 22:05.322
neither of which
will make me feel better.

22:05.357 --> 22:07.324
I am sorry to hear that.

22:08.793 --> 22:11.929
- Do you want to get supper?
- I can't. I have plans.

22:17.334 --> 22:19.168
Thank you, Joan.

22:19.203 --> 22:22.005
- For what?
- I don't know.

22:27.936 --> 22:29.771
Welcome.

22:29.805 --> 22:31.739
Oh, I'm a little damp.

22:31.774 --> 22:33.374
Did it finally rain?

22:33.409 --> 22:36.277
No, but I walked.
This was cold when I left.

22:36.311 --> 22:38.445
You walked from the West Side?

22:39.847 --> 22:42.549
What an incredible space.

22:42.583 --> 22:44.050
Did you do this yourself?

22:44.084 --> 22:46.186
Oh, I had a little help.

22:46.220 --> 22:49.723
Arlene, you read about the
shootings in the park, didn't you?

22:49.757 --> 22:51.825
I'm not gonna let
a few lunatics

22:51.859 --> 22:53.592
ruin a gorgeous night
like this.

23:00.467 --> 23:02.134
Should I go get my script?

23:02.168 --> 23:04.870
Megan, darling,

23:04.904 --> 23:06.739
you're a good actress

23:06.773 --> 23:08.640
on your way to becoming, well,

23:08.674 --> 23:10.442
at least a successful one.

23:10.476 --> 23:12.711
There's nothing I can
tell you about that script.

23:12.745 --> 23:14.679
I came over here because
I'm worried about you.

23:14.714 --> 23:16.748
Am I gonna get fired?

23:18.718 --> 23:20.852
I remember my first job.

23:20.886 --> 23:22.454
Believe it or not, in radio.

23:22.488 --> 23:24.288
"Against the Storm."

23:24.323 --> 23:28.425
Very classy, a lot of
big words, high morals.

23:28.460 --> 23:30.794
And my agent,
who I later learned

23:30.829 --> 23:32.596
was angling
to sign Roger DeKoven,

23:32.630 --> 23:34.665
told me my voice was childish.

23:34.699 --> 23:36.567
And every day I would
vacillate between

23:36.601 --> 23:39.035
"Arlene, you're wonderful"
and "Arlene, you're caca."

23:40.437 --> 23:42.505
Which was it?

23:42.539 --> 23:44.540
Honestly?

23:44.575 --> 23:46.576
I was wonderful.

23:53.517 --> 23:55.050
You should go inside.

23:55.085 --> 23:56.885
You'll get eaten
alive out here.

23:56.919 --> 23:59.220
You know mosquitos ignore me.

23:59.255 --> 24:00.889
In those shorts?

24:05.595 --> 24:07.128
Did you find a bottle?

24:08.664 --> 24:09.865
Maybe.

24:23.712 --> 24:25.946
Cheers.

24:32.586 --> 24:34.854
I loved camp.

24:37.591 --> 24:39.692
I never went.

24:39.727 --> 24:41.594
Yes, you did.

24:43.497 --> 24:46.398
Remember when we went to Lake
Champlain with my parents?

24:48.200 --> 24:50.569
I remember.

24:50.603 --> 24:52.538
And you got in a horrible
fight with my father

24:52.572 --> 24:54.372
about who would
carry the luggage.

24:55.708 --> 24:58.811
And then we went in the
woods and made Sally.

25:01.212 --> 25:03.681
I don't understand her.

25:05.417 --> 25:07.585
Henry says
she's a lot like you.

25:07.619 --> 25:09.720
How would he know?

25:09.755 --> 25:11.989
He says she reminds him of you.

25:12.023 --> 25:14.258
I think she's a lot like you.

25:17.094 --> 25:19.395
Bobby reminds me of my father.

25:19.430 --> 25:21.064
So bossy.

25:23.334 --> 25:26.069
All the teenagers
of the world are in revolt.

25:32.376 --> 25:34.710
What were we like?

25:36.245 --> 25:38.246
You and me?

25:42.251 --> 25:43.953
When I saw you earlier today

25:43.987 --> 25:46.889
I thought for a second,
"Who is that man?"

25:48.424 --> 25:50.692
And I forgot how mad
I was at you.

25:53.729 --> 25:56.664
Ugh, I don't know what's
happened, but I'm all bit up.

26:30.230 --> 26:32.364
Close the door.
You'll let the bugs in.

26:51.517 --> 26:53.450
What are you doing?

26:53.484 --> 26:56.587
Waiting for you
to tell me to stop.

27:10.734 --> 27:13.570
What did you think
when you saw me?

27:13.604 --> 27:16.539
That you are as beautiful
as the day I met you.

27:27.784 --> 27:29.818
So finally I said to Mel,

27:29.852 --> 27:33.121
"I'm either his mother or his girlfriend.
I can't be both."

27:33.155 --> 27:34.823
That's bad writing.

27:34.857 --> 27:37.025
You're so lucky he's at work.

27:37.060 --> 27:40.128
Please, dear, that's a
complex relationship.

27:40.162 --> 27:42.229
But he understands what you do

27:42.263 --> 27:44.098
and he wants you to be great.

27:44.132 --> 27:46.400
And he's always proud of you.
I've seen it.

27:46.434 --> 27:48.970
Don's very proud of you.

27:49.004 --> 27:51.639
You can tell
by how protective he is.

27:53.842 --> 27:56.510
It's been so different.

27:56.544 --> 28:00.614
You know, we worked together
and I left to pursue this.

28:00.648 --> 28:02.682
And he was so encouraging.

28:02.717 --> 28:05.351
And then you
started succeeding.

28:05.385 --> 28:07.320
He's old-fashioned.

28:07.354 --> 28:08.922
He'll get used to it.

28:08.956 --> 28:11.257
I think he did.

28:11.291 --> 28:15.327
And I think he got used
to me not being around

28:15.361 --> 28:18.497
and having a bunch of problems
that he couldn't solve.

28:19.799 --> 28:22.034
And I don't know

28:22.068 --> 28:25.604
if it's him or me, but...

28:25.639 --> 28:27.372
I feel so lonely.

28:33.278 --> 28:34.746
Arlene.

28:34.780 --> 28:36.447
What?

28:36.481 --> 28:37.982
I want to make you feel better.

28:38.017 --> 28:40.451
This isn't the way.

28:41.820 --> 28:43.755
Forget it.

28:46.257 --> 28:48.391
I can't believe you.

28:48.425 --> 28:51.995
I'm trusting you and you're taking
advantage of every private moment.

28:52.030 --> 28:55.132
Well, what was I
supposed to think?

28:56.768 --> 28:58.501
You invited me over.

28:58.536 --> 29:00.070
Your husband's not here.

29:00.104 --> 29:01.937
Two bottles of wine
to go over a scene

29:01.972 --> 29:03.438
a child could understand.

29:03.473 --> 29:05.174
"I'm so lonely."

29:05.208 --> 29:07.843
I work with you and your
husband is my boss.

29:07.878 --> 29:09.478
And now what am I
supposed to do?

29:09.512 --> 29:11.881
Am I gonna be punished
for not doing something

29:11.915 --> 29:13.849
that you won't stop
trying to do?

29:13.884 --> 29:15.918
Megan, it's okay to say no.

29:15.952 --> 29:18.286
But you don't have
to embarrass me.

29:18.320 --> 29:20.955
I'm sorry.

29:20.990 --> 29:23.424
I didn't mean to.

29:23.458 --> 29:24.993
No, stop it.

29:25.027 --> 29:26.795
You're a tease.

29:26.829 --> 29:28.329
Fine.

29:29.765 --> 29:32.200
No, I'm fine
with being a tease.

29:35.236 --> 29:37.171
Well, honey,

29:37.205 --> 29:38.872
just learn the lines.

29:38.907 --> 29:41.809
Two characters is tough,
but you know what Olivier says,

29:41.843 --> 29:43.811
let the wig do the work.

29:45.914 --> 29:48.148
I'm gonna go
before I--

29:48.183 --> 29:51.417
well, it's too late
for that, isn't it?

29:51.451 --> 29:53.086
Thank you for that.

29:54.688 --> 29:56.989
No hard feelings.

29:57.024 --> 29:59.092
Status quo ante bellum.

29:59.126 --> 30:01.594
Everything as it was.

30:22.678 --> 30:24.613
I missed you.

30:35.924 --> 30:37.992
Do you feel guilty?

30:38.026 --> 30:40.128
No.

30:40.162 --> 30:42.630
This happened a long time ago.

30:52.774 --> 30:54.507
Ugh, menthols.

30:56.043 --> 30:57.677
I don't miss that.

31:04.952 --> 31:07.686
Is this what it would have been
like if we'd stayed together?

31:11.291 --> 31:13.558
I don't think about
that anymore.

31:15.028 --> 31:17.062
I'm happy in my life.

31:17.097 --> 31:19.364
Let's just enjoy this.

31:20.633 --> 31:22.600
But you used to?

31:24.469 --> 31:26.537
What are you thinking
right now?

31:27.973 --> 31:30.241
I'm thinking about
how different you are,

31:30.276 --> 31:32.243
before and after.

31:34.546 --> 31:37.115
I love the way you look at me
when you're like this.

31:38.683 --> 31:40.951
But then I watch it decay.

31:42.253 --> 31:45.422
I can only hold
your attention so long.

31:50.494 --> 31:52.395
Why is sex

31:52.430 --> 31:55.564
the definition of being
close to someone?

31:55.598 --> 31:57.800
I don't know,

31:57.835 --> 31:59.768
but it is for me.

31:59.803 --> 32:01.871
It is for most people.

32:03.506 --> 32:06.342
Just because you climb a mountain
doesn't mean you love it.

32:06.376 --> 32:08.044
Climbing a mountain?

32:08.078 --> 32:10.345
Is that what
making love is to you?

32:10.379 --> 32:13.448
If we'd lied here together
with you in my arms,

32:13.482 --> 32:15.917
I would have felt
just as close.

32:17.286 --> 32:19.287
Not the rest of it.
I don't know.

32:21.657 --> 32:23.959
I don't know.

32:23.993 --> 32:26.126
It doesn't mean
that much to me.

32:28.096 --> 32:30.264
Is it the same with Megan?

32:32.433 --> 32:34.235
Why do you want
to talk about that?

32:34.269 --> 32:36.636
That poor girl.

32:41.442 --> 32:44.844
She doesn't know
that loving you

32:44.879 --> 32:47.546
is the worst way to get to you.

33:07.300 --> 33:09.667
Are you sure you don't
want to just hold me?

33:32.456 --> 33:34.424
Oh, Jesus.

33:34.458 --> 33:37.360
Oh, thank God.
What are you doing in here?

33:37.395 --> 33:39.062
I was just fixing the window.

33:39.096 --> 33:40.563
What the hell happened here?

33:40.597 --> 33:42.732
I'll replace it tomorrow
when I get back from work.

33:42.766 --> 33:44.367
Because you're leaving me here

33:44.402 --> 33:46.135
after someone threw a rock
through our window?

33:46.169 --> 33:47.736
That's not what happened.

33:47.770 --> 33:50.672
Well, I came in here and there's
glass all over the floor

33:50.706 --> 33:52.942
and you're holding a rock.

33:52.976 --> 33:55.610
I'm tired of being
interrogated in my own home.

33:55.645 --> 33:58.380
Do you think they saw you
talking to the police?

33:58.415 --> 34:00.449
If you're gonna let
your imagination run wild,

34:00.483 --> 34:01.650
come to the paper
with me tonight.

34:01.684 --> 34:03.818
Abe, I have to go
to work tomorrow.

34:03.852 --> 34:05.286
And this is our bedroom.

34:05.321 --> 34:07.255
Someone was in our yard.

34:07.289 --> 34:09.123
I'm really scared here.

34:09.158 --> 34:11.592
And you're going to protect me?
You only have one hand.

34:14.396 --> 34:18.764
You're right.
You're right.

34:18.799 --> 34:21.969
We'll start looking.
Put it on the market.

34:25.606 --> 34:27.540
You'd really do that for me?

34:27.574 --> 34:30.444
Maybe we're not cut out
to be pioneers.

34:41.955 --> 34:45.123
Sleep in the parlor if you're worried.
I won't wake you.

34:50.029 --> 34:51.329
Hello?

34:51.364 --> 34:54.699
You took a four-year-old
to see "Planet of the Apes"?

34:54.733 --> 34:57.302
He's been having
nightmares all night.

34:57.336 --> 34:58.769
Hold on, hold on.

34:58.804 --> 35:00.472
He wanted to see that.

35:00.506 --> 35:02.240
He doesn't decide that.

35:02.274 --> 35:04.142
Well, Don took his kid.

35:04.176 --> 35:07.344
Don Draper, Father of the Year.

35:07.379 --> 35:09.313
Margaret, honey, he loved it.

35:09.347 --> 35:12.116
Put him on, I'll do Dr. Zaius again.
He laughs like an idiot.

35:12.150 --> 35:14.751
The Forbidden
Zone was once a paradise.

35:14.785 --> 35:16.720
You're not funny, Daddy.

35:16.754 --> 35:19.789
We'll probably have to get rid of
the dog; he's that afraid of fur.

35:21.526 --> 35:23.994
Listen, I saw "The Golem"
when I was his age.

35:24.028 --> 35:25.795
You don't even know
what scary is.

35:25.830 --> 35:27.463
I was fine.
It's not my fault.

35:27.498 --> 35:30.800
Yeah, you're right.
It's my fault.

35:30.835 --> 35:33.102
For letting you talk me
into having a four-year-old

35:33.137 --> 35:34.571
watch another
four-year-old.

35:34.605 --> 35:37.641
Listen to me, young lady,
you calm down this minute.

35:37.675 --> 35:39.441
No, Daddy, you listen to me.

35:39.475 --> 35:41.844
You can keep up your fantasy
of acting like a father,

35:41.878 --> 35:43.445
but your grandfather
days are done.

35:43.479 --> 35:46.448
I'm sorry you're upset.
I'm coming over.

35:46.482 --> 35:48.283
- I'll calm him down.
- <i>No.</i>

35:48.317 --> 35:50.252
And call Mother next time
you want to see him

35:50.286 --> 35:52.487
'cause she has to be there.

36:22.283 --> 36:25.151
- Morning.
- Good morning.

36:25.186 --> 36:26.786
Good to see you.

36:50.144 --> 36:52.879
It's such a project
going to the beach.

36:52.913 --> 36:54.380
Can I go get Kevin?

36:54.414 --> 36:56.082
Let him sleep a little more.

36:56.117 --> 36:58.251
I'd love to get one
of those summer rentals.

36:58.285 --> 37:00.820
Doesn't Pete Campbell
have a beach house?

37:02.089 --> 37:03.656
I wouldn't ask him
for anything.

37:03.690 --> 37:06.191
- Don't you like him?
- It's not that.

37:07.527 --> 37:09.028
Actually,
he's the only person there

37:09.062 --> 37:10.663
who's never broken
a promise to me.

37:10.697 --> 37:12.765
He's a very generous person.

37:12.799 --> 37:15.067
And frankly, I think
he's having a rough time.

37:15.101 --> 37:17.269
So he told you
about his mother?

37:17.303 --> 37:19.737
No, I wish he would have.
What's wrong?

37:19.772 --> 37:22.040
He needs a nurse.

37:22.074 --> 37:24.341
He's not gonna ask you.
He's too ashamed.

37:24.376 --> 37:27.011
She back from the track already?

37:27.046 --> 37:30.048
Ugh, she must have
forgotten her keys.

37:32.651 --> 37:34.518
Oh, hello, Roger.

37:36.988 --> 37:39.389
- Who are you?
- It's me, Bob Benson.

37:39.423 --> 37:41.457
From the office.

37:43.460 --> 37:44.995
What are you doing here?

37:45.029 --> 37:47.430
Oh, I was out shopping

37:47.464 --> 37:50.167
and I realized I had
misplaced some paperwork.

37:50.201 --> 37:52.634
And I, uh--

37:52.669 --> 37:54.403
what are you two doing?

37:54.437 --> 37:56.038
We're leaving for the beach.

37:56.073 --> 37:58.174
- You know what? I should go get the car.
- Good idea.

37:58.208 --> 38:00.242
No, Mr. Sterling
is just leaving.

38:01.912 --> 38:04.013
Roger, I'm sure
this can wait till Monday.

38:04.047 --> 38:07.015
Sure, absolutely.
Sorry about that, Bob.

38:07.049 --> 38:09.283
I guess we're all a little bit
out of context right now.

38:09.318 --> 38:11.119
I take no offense.

38:22.364 --> 38:24.198
Didn't know you were friends.

38:24.232 --> 38:27.134
Some people never stop working.

38:27.168 --> 38:29.636
I'm going to freshen up
and we'll get out of here.

38:34.675 --> 38:37.111
<i>Hey, get off our lawn!</i>

38:59.098 --> 39:01.099
What's going on?

39:01.134 --> 39:03.502
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

39:03.536 --> 39:05.070
Jesus!

39:05.104 --> 39:08.240
Why didn't you say something?

39:08.275 --> 39:10.576
- What do I do?
- Don't pull it out.

39:13.379 --> 39:16.781
- If I don't make it--
- Stop it.

39:16.815 --> 39:20.351
You're going to make it.
He's going to make it.

39:24.390 --> 39:27.457
Look, I don't want you to think
this is about what you did.

39:28.660 --> 39:30.827
It was an accident.
I feel horrible.

39:30.861 --> 39:33.463
No, you're scared.

39:34.865 --> 39:38.034
You're a scared person
who hides behind complacence--

39:38.068 --> 39:39.869
cy.

39:39.904 --> 39:42.138
Save your strength. You're
not making any sense.

39:42.173 --> 39:44.173
I don't know why
I thought you'd be braver.

39:44.207 --> 39:47.075
You're... in advertising.

39:47.110 --> 39:50.413
Don't do this right now.
I said I was sorry.

39:52.282 --> 39:56.251
Your activities are offensive
to my every waking moment.

39:56.286 --> 39:58.287
I'm sorry...

40:00.055 --> 40:02.089
but you'll always be the enemy.

40:04.493 --> 40:06.294
Are you breaking up with me?

40:10.766 --> 40:12.634
Got to hand it to you.

40:14.303 --> 40:16.837
You gave me a great ending
to my article.

40:42.162 --> 40:44.263
Oh, you're back.

40:49.535 --> 40:51.035
Did you have fun?

40:51.070 --> 40:53.372
I missed you.

40:55.174 --> 40:57.576
Well, I miss you all the time.

41:01.180 --> 41:04.782
I don't know when I started
pretending like everything was sunny.

41:11.956 --> 41:14.558
I don't know where you've gone,

41:14.593 --> 41:16.594
but I'm here.

41:18.963 --> 41:22.599
I keep trying to make things
the way they used to be,

41:22.633 --> 41:24.901
but I don't know how.

41:24.935 --> 41:27.103
And maybe that's stupid

41:27.137 --> 41:29.672
or young to think
like that, but...

41:31.975 --> 41:34.277
something has to change.

41:37.414 --> 41:39.147
Megan...

41:45.622 --> 41:47.589
You're right.

41:47.624 --> 41:49.591
I haven't been here.

42:18.953 --> 42:20.654
Roger, please.

42:20.688 --> 42:22.589
Come on, just take it.

42:22.623 --> 42:24.990
They're Lincoln Logs.

42:25.024 --> 42:27.626
I thought maybe he'd build
his mother a house.

42:27.661 --> 42:29.562
You can't drop in
on me like that.

42:29.596 --> 42:31.196
But I want to.

42:31.230 --> 42:34.333
Oh, Roger, I'm so sorry,

42:34.367 --> 42:35.968
but you can't do this.

42:36.002 --> 42:37.369
Why not?

42:37.403 --> 42:39.671
Because it's too confusing.

42:39.705 --> 42:41.873
For Kevin.
You know.

42:41.907 --> 42:45.242
But I'm his father.

42:45.277 --> 42:47.278
No, his father is Greg.

42:47.312 --> 42:48.880
But I'm here.

42:50.649 --> 42:52.617
For now.

42:52.651 --> 42:56.353
But every day Greg
is some hero out there.

42:56.387 --> 42:59.389
And I'd rather him think
that is the man in his life.

42:59.423 --> 43:02.626
Who's gonna watch TV with him?
Bob Bunson?

43:02.660 --> 43:04.695
I just want to be around.

43:04.729 --> 43:07.430
I know you want to.

43:07.465 --> 43:09.700
But I can't count on that.

43:19.710 --> 43:21.677
Thank you for the gift.

43:32.588 --> 43:36.590
Something delicate
has come to my attention.

43:37.659 --> 43:39.160
Have a seat.

43:41.096 --> 43:42.897
I...

43:42.931 --> 43:45.733
I've really debated whether
to bring this up with you

43:45.767 --> 43:49.170
because I don't want to put
you in a strange position

43:49.204 --> 43:53.140
and in the end
it's probably just gossip.

43:56.677 --> 43:58.412
It's come to my attention

43:58.446 --> 44:01.348
that you may be in need
of a nurse for your mother.

44:01.382 --> 44:03.650
Joan had no right
to tell you that.

44:05.053 --> 44:07.086
His name is Manolo Colón.

44:07.120 --> 44:09.688
He's an army-trained
registered nurse

44:09.722 --> 44:11.490
and he's available now
only because

44:11.525 --> 44:14.060
he's brought my father
back to full health.

44:18.331 --> 44:21.167
Is he Spanish from Spain?
Because otherwise Mother will refuse.

44:21.201 --> 44:23.435
He's very well-bred.

44:26.638 --> 44:29.006
And don't blame Joan.

44:29.041 --> 44:30.675
She was concerned about you

44:30.709 --> 44:32.743
and had exhausted her resources

44:32.778 --> 44:34.512
and is well aware
that your well-being

44:34.547 --> 44:36.614
is also an interest of mine.

44:48.126 --> 44:49.226
Good morning.

44:49.260 --> 44:51.661
- Is he in?
- Yes, just a minute.

44:51.696 --> 44:53.730
It's okay.

44:56.166 --> 44:58.734
Hi.
Good morning.

44:58.768 --> 45:00.769
Good morning.

45:00.804 --> 45:03.706
I just wanted to--

45:03.740 --> 45:05.908
I needed to talk to you.

45:07.611 --> 45:09.378
Peggy, what's wrong?

45:11.214 --> 45:13.982
I...

45:14.016 --> 45:16.050
Abe got stabbed.

45:16.085 --> 45:18.620
My goodness. Is he okay?
What happened?

45:18.654 --> 45:20.788
He's going to be fine.

45:22.258 --> 45:23.758
But it's over.

45:26.228 --> 45:27.928
We're done.

45:31.399 --> 45:35.744
I'm sorry to hear that.

45:36.160 --> 45:38.394
You are?

45:39.896 --> 45:42.064
You'll find someone else.

45:42.098 --> 45:44.999
And whoever he is,
he's lucky to have you.

45:48.704 --> 45:50.472
Thank you.

45:50.506 --> 45:52.274
You ready to get to work?

45:52.308 --> 45:53.675
Excuse me?

45:53.709 --> 45:56.478
It's Monday morning, Peggy.
Brand-new week.

46:02.651 --> 46:05.519
Morning.
How was your weekend?

46:05.554 --> 46:07.621
How'd it go with Fleischmann's?

46:07.656 --> 46:10.224
They just called.
Full speed ahead.

46:10.258 --> 46:12.259
Good work.

46:14.062 --> 46:15.662
Round up the team.

46:19.600 --> 46:22.502
<i>♪ I walk along</i>
<i>the city streets ♪</i>

46:22.536 --> 46:27.139
<i>♪ You used to walk</i>
<i>along with me ♪</i>

46:27.174 --> 46:29.475
<i>♪ And every step I take ♪</i>

46:29.510 --> 46:33.378
<i>♪ Recalls how much</i>
<i>in love we used to be ♪</i>

46:33.413 --> 46:37.782
<i>♪ Oh, how can I forget you ♪</i>

46:37.817 --> 46:42.187
<i>♪ When there is always</i>
<i>something there to remind me? ♪</i>

46:42.188 --> 46:44.688
